sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I746372
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This construct is used to screen the level of induction of the P2 ogr activator on the PF promoter.
Note that the I746350 does contain a RBS.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: I746313 was put upstream of I746322
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stefan Milde

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I746322
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: GFP under control of PP promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is used to screen the level of induction of the PP promoter (I746362). The PP promoter is induced by a class of phage activators (P2 ogr: I746350, PSP3pag: I746351, phiR73 delta: I746352).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The PP promoter was put upstream of I13504.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stefan Milde

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I746313
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: arabinose induced expression of P2 ogr and mRFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: In this device the arabinose induced pBAD/araC promoter controls expression of the P2 ogr activator and mRFP. It is used to induce P2 ogr expression.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: I746307 was put upstream of I13507
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Cambridge iGEM 2007 team

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: GFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: green fluorescent protein derived from jellyfish Aequeora victoria wild-type GFP (SwissProt: P42212
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: GFP (mut3b) [note that this part does not have a barcode]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: jcbraff

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I13507
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Built by Josh as an intermediate in screening plasmid construction.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: jkm

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I746307
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: P2 ogr under control of pBAD/araC promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a construction intermediate. It consists of the arabinose-induced pBAD/araC promoter and the P2 ogr activator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This is a construction intermediate without a terminator. The I746350 was put downstream of I0500.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stefan Milde

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I746362
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the PP promoter taken from the P2 phage genome. It is an inducible promoter that is activated by a class of activators, including P2 ogr (I746350), PSP3 pag (I746351) and phiR73 delta (I746352). These different activators should cause different levels of activity of the PP promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stefan Milde

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mRFP1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: **highly** engineered mutant of red fluorescent protein from Discosoma striata (coral)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Campbell et al., PNAS v99 p7877 URL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: monomeric RFP: Red Fluorescent Protein. Excitation peak: 584 nm Emission peak: 607 nm
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
TAATAA double stop codon added (DE).
Four silent mutations made to remove three EcoRI sites and one PstI site: A28G, A76G, A349G, G337A.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I746350
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: plasmid DNA supplied by Prof. Richard Calendar, University of California.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The ogr activator taken from P2 phage acts on a class of inducible promoters (parts I746360 to I746365), inducing their activity to varying degrees. The part sequence does already contain a ribosome binding site (B0034)!
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The part does contain a RBS (B0034) already.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stefan Milde
